rComments: She seems to be extremely conscientious, and she is very helpful and very nice.

Professor Dinkova-Bruun is a great person, but her lectures are not structured well. Clarity was a problem in her lectures, and especially in her assignments. When a student complained about the lack of clarity, she brushed it off, and said she was looking for creativety. NOT HELPFUL.

VERY interesting course (medieval book). She was really into the material and came up with these great anecdotes. Good sense of humour, made medieval books fun! Loved making the little book for ourselves. Hard marker on the essay front: ask what she wants, beforehand.
Not as easy as she seems but overall, she's a cool professor.  The course is also very interesting.  Take it if you want a new challenge.
Excellent professor.  Knows her stuff, passionate about it and teaches it to students well.  SMC211 is only a great course because of her!  Assignment were too vague and difficult though.
